race.comment: JADE DIVISION (15) brings a solid set of figures here deep into the prep. Sat on the speed on the backup when faded late to run sixth. Assess on the game performance when second at Bathurst two back with the 58kg. Top three prospect. IVY DIVA (11) recent efforts have been better than they appear on paper and finally comes up with a low gate. Went back when she failed to get into the contest finishing tenth over 1300m at Scone. The run two back had merit. Value chance. MISSY MOSS (8) tongue-tie goes on, and a win looks imminent. Stripped fitter second up when a narrow third over 1200m at Warren. Tags the fast speed and she finds a suitable race. ANDALE (2) continued where he left off last prep when returning for a slick on pace win over 1100m at Wellington. Toughened over the break and gets his chance at this trip.
